{"lemma":"خَطِيرٌ","slug":"خَطِيرٌ","root":"خ.ط.ر","root_slug":"خ-ط-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ط-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11006"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"great"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"high"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"powerful and respected"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of high rank"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"important, weighty","examples":[{"text":"مَوْضُوعٌ خَطِيرٌ","english":"Important subject"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dangerous, risky"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xa.tˤiːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11006","headword_ar":"خَطِيرٌ","root":"xTr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"falling of a camel's tail between the parts above his thighs, when he moves it about;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1, first sentence;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xTAr","text_ar":"خطار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA: in which the latter is written without any syll. signs.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel's nose-rein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a nose-rein by which a she-camel is led:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, K:) these, says Meyd, are one and the same thing. (TA.) It is related in a trad. of 'Alee that he said to [ a mistake for “ respecting ”] 'Ammár,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jur~uwA lahu AlxaTiyra maA A@nojar~a lakumo","text_ar":"جُرُّوا لَهُ الخَطِيرَ مَا ا@نْجَرَّ لَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pull ye his noserein as long as it will be pulled by you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as some relate the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA jar~ahu lakumo","text_ar":"مَا جَرَّهُ لَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as he pulls it to you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: meaning follow him as long as there is ground for doing so: or, accord. to some, as Sh says, act patiently towards 'Ammar as long as he acts patiently towards you: Meyd mentions it as a proverb. (TA.)       -A3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eminent; noble; of high rank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"characterized by rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuTorN","text_ar":"خُطْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTiyruwna","text_ar":"خَطِيرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) And (assumed tropical:)  Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN xaTiyrN","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ خَطِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an affair, of high account"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ignoble; of low rank;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contemptible."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Msb.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaTarN","text_ar":"خَطَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["Kr","Sh","K","Msb","TA","S","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}